# {{ hostname }} hosting wrapper

This directory contains homesrvctl-owned hosting files for an existing source tree.

- source path: `{{ source_path }}`
- wrapper family: `{{ family }}`
- detected family: `{{ detected_family }}`
- internal service port: `{{ service_port }}`
- docker network: `{{ docker_network }}`

The source directory remains app-owned. Keep application code changes there, and keep hosting wrapper changes in this directory.

## Run

```bash
homesrvctl up {{ hostname }}
homesrvctl doctor {{ hostname }}
```
